The purpose of this program is to explore genetic algoriths in a scientific context, specifically, to minimize the residuary resistance of a ship and thereby search for an accurate set of parameters that will do so. A basic linear regression model was first used to predict the residuary resistance (r^2 ~0.975) and consequently a genetic algorithm was used to search the parameter space for the optimal combination.

It was found that in the dataset the instance with the lowest residuary resistance was 0.01. The genetic algorithm yielded a minimum residuary of 0.004. This suggests that the genetic algorithm successfully explored regions of the parameter space beyond the observed data and identified a potentially more hydrodynamically efficient hull configuration according to the regression model. However, because the predicted optimum lies outside the range of observed target values, it should be validated using higher-fidelity simulations or experimental testing before being considered physically achievable.